remarks: "Datisi", one of the syllogisms of Aristotelian logic.  All ` ph ` is ` ps ` , and some ` ph ` is ` ch ` , therefore some ` ch ` is ` ps ` . (In Aristotelian notation, AII-3:  MaP and MiS therefore SiP.) (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 28-Aug-2016.)
statement:
datisi.maj $e |- A. x ( ph -> ps ) $.
datisi.min $e |- E. x ( ph /\ ch ) $.
datisi $p |- E. x ( ch /\ ps ) $.
